      • entityMode

        public final AnyValueWriter.EntityMode entityMode()
        Description copied from interface: AnyValueWriter
        Returns the wanted AnyValueWriter.EntityMode of this AnyValueWriter. A returned AnyValueWriter.EntityMode.REFERENCE signals to all entity-values that they should callback using AnyValueWriter.writeNodeReference(long) or AnyValueWriter.writeRelationshipReference(long) even if the whole entity is available. A returned AnyValueWriter.EntityMode.FULL signals to all entity-values that they can callback using either AnyValueWriter.writeNodeReference(long), AnyValueWriter.writeNode(long, TextArray, MapValue), AnyValueWriter.writeRelationshipReference(long) or AnyValueWriter.writeRelationship(long, long, long, TextValue, MapValue) depending on how much information is available to the value instance.
        Specified by:
        entityMode in interface AnyValueWriter<E extends Exception>
